observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive to:

direct the Municipal Treasurer to take necessary steps to strengthen the tax collection strategies of the agency;
direct the Municipal Treasurer to establish a precise monitoring of delinquent tax payers; 
direct the Municipal Assessor to recommend to the sanggunian the strategies relating to tax ordinance and revenue measures for the collection of RPT; and
direct the Sangguniang Bayan of the Municipality to support the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Assessor in strengthening the agency’s collection strategies.

We recommended and management agreed that the Local Chief Executive
direct the LDRRM Officer to strive for the timely and full implementation of LDRRM-related PPAs to achieved the goals and objectives of the fund and the desired benefits;
direct the Municipal Accountant and the LDRRMO to refrain from charging expenses to LDRRMF that are not in accordance with Section 3.0 of COA Circular 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012;
require the Mun. Accountant and the MGSO to submit the required documents for further evaluation of the transactions pursuant to Section 4(6) of PD No. 1445 and to ensure that all the supporting documents are properly signed and provided with complete information.
